<% content_for :title, "Data Deletion — Sales Gorilla" %>

<h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl">Data Deletion Instructions</h1>
<p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-soft">Last updated: June 10, 2026</p>

<div class="legal mt-8">
  <p>
    Sales Gorilla (operated by <strong>Tecaudex</strong>) lets you delete data you have
    stored, and request deletion of personal information we hold. This page explains how,
    including for data received through the Meta (Facebook/Instagram) Lead Ads integration.
  </p>

  <h2>Disconnecting a Facebook Page</h2>
  <p>
    If your organization connected a Facebook Page, an administrator can disconnect it at any
    time from <strong>Settings → Features → Meta Lead Ads → Disconnect</strong>. Disconnecting
    immediately stops new leads from syncing and removes the stored Page access token from our
    systems.
  </p>

  <h2>Deleting lead and contact records</h2>
  <p>
    Leads imported into your CRM (including those captured via Meta Lead Ads) can be deleted
    directly inside the app by an authorized user. Deleting a contact removes its record and the
    associated lead-capture data from your workspace.
  </p>

  <h2>Requesting a full deletion</h2>
  <p>
    To request deletion of all personal data associated with you or your organization, email
    <a href="mailto:privacy@salesgorilla.app">privacy@salesgorilla.app</a> from the address
    associated with your account, or with enough detail for us to locate the data, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The name and email/phone associated with the data, and</li>
    <li>The organization (workspace) or Facebook Page the data relates to, if known.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We will verify the request and delete the relevant personal information within
    <strong>30 days</strong>, except where we are required to retain it to comply with a legal
    obligation. We will confirm by email once the deletion is complete.
  </p>

  <h2>End users of a Customer’s lead forms</h2>
  <p>
    If you submitted your information through a business’s Facebook/Instagram lead form and that
    business uses Sales Gorilla, that business controls your data. You may contact them directly,
    or email us at <a href="mailto:privacy@salesgorilla.app">privacy@salesgorilla.app</a> and we
    will route the request to the appropriate organization and assist with deletion.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-6">
    See also our <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path %> and
    <%= link_to "Terms of Service", terms_path %>.
  </p>
</div>
